							h2(style="font-size: medium; font-weight: bold") What is a strong password ?
							p A password that is difficult to detect by both humans and computer programs, effectively protecting data from unauthorized access. A strong password consists:
							ul
								li At least 15 characters.
								li Does not contain your user name, real name, or company name.
								li Includes Numbers, Symbols, Capital Letters, and Lower-Case Letters.
								li Does not contain a complete dictionary word.
								li Different from previous passwords.
							h2(style="font-size: medium; font-weight: bold") What is a bad password ?
							p A password that is easy for humans or computers to guess.
							ul
								li Your login or username.
								li Your name, your friend’s name, your family member’s name, or a common name.
								li Your own birthday.
								li A keyboard pattern, such as qwerty, asdfghjkl, or 12345678.
								li Like your previous passwords.
							p These are bad passwords because:
							ul
								li Malicious attackers can guess that your password is your birthday or the name of someone you know or some other piece of information related to you.
								li Malicious attackers can program computers to repeatedly guess that your password is made up of one or more words in a wordlist or default password list. This is called a dictionary attack.
							h2(style="font-size: medium; font-weight: bold") Keep your password secret
							p Even good passwords can become bad passwords if they aren't handled correctly.
							ul
								li Never tell your password to anyone (this includes significant others, roommates, coworkers, etc.). If you need to grant someone access to your server, set up a separate username and password for that person.
								li Never write your password down, especially not anywhere near your computer.
								li Do not store your password in a plain text file on your computer.
								li Change your password regularly and never reuse it.


